.SH "NAME"
gl_LocalInvocationIndex \- contains the local linear index of work item currently being operated on by a compute shader
.SH "DECLARATION"
in\ \&uint\ \&gl_LocalInvocationIndex\ \&;.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
In the compute language,
\fIgl_LocalInvocationIndex\fR
is a derived input variable containing the 1\-dimensional linearized index of the work invocation within the work group that the current shader is executing on\&. The value of
\fIgl_LocalInvocationIndex\fR
is equal to
\fIgl_LocalInvocationID\&.z\fR
*
\fIgl_WorkGroupSize\&.x\fR
*
\fIgl_WorkGroupSize\&.y\fR
+
\fIgl_LocalInvocationID\&.y\fR
*
\fIgl_WorkGroupSize\&.x\fR
+
\fIgl_LocalInvocationID\&.x\fR\&.
